A.Explaination of implemented features
	checked whether the schema entered by user is valid or not.
	for example,since schema is a character so it must be of 		length one.

	checked a condition where if a user put only '-' instead of '-d'(for example) it throws an exception

	User needs to enter some argument (atleast one),else it will 		throw an exception

	if schema is empty,program throws an exception

B.1 Requirements
	user must enter some argument

B.2 Execution
	Open terminal from /home/user/folder/src/com/cleancoder/args
	
to compile :
javac ArgsException.java ArgumentMarshaler.java 	BooleanArgumentMarshaler.java DoubleArgumentMarshaler.java MapArgumentMarshaler.java StringArrayArgumentMarshaler.java StringArgumentMarshaler.java IntegerArgumentMarshaler.java Args.java ArgsMain.java 

after that you need to be at src i.e. /home/user/folder/src

to run program:
	 java com.cleancoder.args.ArgsMain -l -p 56 -d any_String   -m key:value -a 99.99 -s hello -s world

B3. Unit test

test for all cases are present in ArgsTest.java

go to /home/user/folder/test

to run:
java -cp "lib/junit-4.13.jar:lib/hamcrest-core-1.3.jar:build/jar/args.jar" ./test/com/cleancoder/args/ArgsTest.java

C:
code is self explainatory
created methods instead of writing big functions
use error handling







	
	

